![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/fdd8b084-2201-4ca1-aff1-7cc891fec677/311.jpg?format=original)

Gather round young children, as we tell the tale of the last film of the DCEU. Aquaman And The Lost Kingdom certainly had some big shoes to follow, with the first Aquaman film breaking $1 billion dollars at the box office, but in a post-covid era of Superhero Fatigue can the King of Atlantis hold back the waves of apathy towards the genre as whole? Join us as we discuss not only the last DCEU movie to exist, but the last theatrically released comic book movie of 2023, on the LAST EPISODE OF THE MAJOR ISSUES PODCAST FOR THE YEAR!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

Send us feedback at **ComicBookClique@Gmail.com!** You Are Worthy! 

